The paper deals with incentive-compatible information elicitation from strategic agents, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves probabilistic beliefs and accuracy in predictions, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new mechanism for scoring rules, which could be of interest to researchers in data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
